This portion of the library is a standardized informatica API helper.

It's initiated by passing along a username and password.

Any errors that are thrown as a result of Informatica failures will raise an InformaticaError.

```
from wcp_library.informatica import InformaticaSession

informatica_session = InformaticaSession("Example-User", "Example-Pass")
```

## Methods
### get_tasks

`def get_tasks(self, task_type: str) -> dict:`

Returns a task dictionary containing all the tasks with the specified task type.

You can find the list of task types (here)[https://jsapi.apiary.io/apis/cloudrestapi/reference/job/list-of-tasks.html].

The API endpoint documentation with expected return values is [here](https://docs.informatica.com/integration-cloud/b2b-gateway/current-version/rest-api-reference/platform-rest-api-version-2-resources/tasks.html).

```
mtt_tasks = informatica_session.get_tasks("MTT")
```

### get_task_id

`def get_task_id(self, task_name: str, task_type: str) -> str:`

This function piggy-backs off get_tasks() to find the associated taskId.

```
mtt_task_id = informatica_session.get_task_id("Test-Task", "MTT")
```

### is_task_running

`def is_task_running(self, task_id: str) -> tuple[bool, datetime]:`

Determines whether or not a task is running based off it's taskId. It returns a boolean value (true = running, false = not), and the local time (MT) the task started running.

```
is_running, start_time = informatica_session.is_task_running(mtt_task_id)
```

### run_job

`def run_job(self, task_id: str, task_type: str) -> str:`

Initiates a job to run on the informatica instance, returns the job's jobId.

```
job_id = informatica_session.run_job(mtt_task_id, "MTT")
```

### wait_until_job_finish

`def wait_until_job_finish(self, run_id: str) -> datetime:`

Waits for the informatica job to finish running, and returns it's end time.

```
job_end_time = informatica_session.wait_until_job_finish(job_id)
```

### get_connection_details

`def get_connection_details(self) -> dict:`

Returns all of the connections inside the informatica instance.

The API endpoint documentation with expected return values is [here](https://docs.informatica.com/integration-cloud/b2b-gateway/current-version/rest-api-reference/data-integration-rest-api/connections.html).

```
all_informatica_connections = informatica_session.get_connection_details()
```

### get_all_mapping_details

`def get_all_mapping_details(self) -> dict:`

Returns all of the mappings inside the informatica instance.

The API endpoint documentation with expected return values is [here](https://docs.informatica.com/integration-cloud/b2b-gateway/current-version/rest-api-reference/data-integration-rest-api/mappings.html).

```
all_informatica_connections = informatica_session.get_all_mapping_details()
```

### get_mapping_details

`def get_mapping_details(self, mapping_id: str) -> dict:`

Returns the details of the specified mapping inside the informatica instance.

The API endpoint documentation with expected return values is [here](https://docs.informatica.com/integration-cloud/b2b-gateway/current-version/rest-api-reference/data-integration-rest-api/mappings.html).

```
mapping_details = informatica_session.get_mapping_details(mapping_id)
```

## Exceptions

### InformaticaError

`class InformaticaError(Exception)`

Raised whenever an Informatica API call fails (non-200 response, login failure, or job failure state). All methods on `InformaticaSession` raise this exception on error rather than returning ``None``/``False``.
